relation.text: went to Miſs Gunning & Miſs Tryon at 3 . my Uncle in ye Eveg . -- 28 Thursday
came home . alone ye rest of ye Eveg Sunday
1782 -- Lord Napier to Breakfast -- Lady Dartrey . Doctr Turton Madm . de La Fite & her daughter Mr & Mrs & Miſs Hamilton Mr Devaynes call
Tuesday 3 d . Mr. Hamilton in ye . Morng & Lord Napier I went
1782 Lord Napier Mr Fisher to Breakfast -- Mr Devaynes came
s for part of ye . Eveg . 11 Decbr Wednesday
took away 39 Pictures for 200 £ . to be ) paid 2 Months
am settled -- only ourselves 12 th . Decbr 1782
Bed . after supper talkd over ye . Character of Miſs G . & amp ; c & c Mr. Cumberland . & c . Decbr . 20 th . Friday
1782 After Breakfast . Mrs. B Glover came
came home the Veseys call 'd -- Mr Devaynes & Mr. Jackson Sup 'd with us Decbr- 23 d Monday
s letters . Recd . a letter from Gray 26 th Decbr Thursday
Quarters at Shaftsbury Dorset : Lord Napier came
s affairs & c & c Decbr 27 th .. Friday
Spendlove at supper . 28 th . Decbr Saturday
pour le Ciel , & que l'Honnête homme est celui qui ne craint ni la critique , ni l'examen . Decbr . 29 th . Sunday
told me of ye Loan Decbr . 30 th . Monday
Concluded ye . Year very happily 1 st Janry . 1783
set me down at home at 10 Miſs 3 rd . Friday
read Prayers to Lady F Harpur & c me home at 10 -- Mr . Manners & Miſs WKing at Supper . Sunday
came home in a Chair . 6 th . Monday
saw him in ye Morning 7 th . Tuesday
wrote to Mr. Glover 8 th Wednesday
read to him before , & after Suppe r -- ye . American book Hist : Nantucket . Mr. Glover -- Miſs Glover -- Son -- Mr. G . -- Lady Caroline Vernon 10 Tuesday
sat up wth Coll Hamilton after ye rest retired talk of America Tuesday 14 Jan
read out frm . 7 till 10 -- An Oriental Comedy written 30 years ago
Monday . After B . Mr. Barnard & I went
sat sometime with Lord Stormont talk 'd of Mr. Glover 22 d . Wednesday
sat an hour wth- Coll Goldsworthy -- talk 'd of his dau ghter & c & c & c 23 d . Janry . Thursday
parted with Mrs. Jackson to day -- Monday
Tuesday 4 -- Ldy . Dartrey Mrs Chapone Mr. Glover in ye Morng & Glover & c & c all day -- sat
Wednesday -- my Uncle call 'd did not see
went to Mrs. Lenton in ye Morng 6 th Thursday
wrote ye . rest of ye . Eveg . . 13 Friday
Thursday Mr. G . in ye Morng . I wrote
came home & sup 'd with Sheridan Thursday March 20
sat with Mrs. Delany & ye Dowr . Ducheſs of Portland till 12 Lord Dartmouth for ½ of an hour in ye Eveg Wedn . 26 March 1783
'd came home at 12 we had Mr. J . Coach Friday
gave me a Meſsage to Mrs. Lake Sunday
March 1783 Mr Skeffington & my Uncle in ye . Morng . . din 'd
sat up till past 3 in ye . Morning . writing & c & c . April 1
Tuesday . Mrs Handcock in ye . Morng . . Miſs Clarkes came
read in my room Lady Gower call 'd when I was out Satry 5 th . April 1783
staid with Mr. Glover till 11 Sunday
1783 . Miſs Gunning Lady C Peachey Miſs H . . Miſs H . call
begun a Novel & c with Mrs Vesey April 8
Thursday . Miſs Hamilton Lady A Greville call 'd did not see
April 1783 in ye . Morng . Miſs Gunning Mrs. Milbanke -- Mrs. Delany Rapin Queen Anne -- din 'd at home ye . Veseys read
Wednesday 23 d -- Mrs. Turton & Miſs KnowSley in ye . Morng . -- din 'd at home -- Miſsrs Jackson came
April 1783 . Mr Glover . Mr Jackson & Miſs H call 'd did not see
April 1783 . Buller call 'd did not see
s -- only him & his 2 daughters interesting conversation Sunday
April 1783 . after dinner upon Education -- ye . present fashions & c -- staid
s sup 'd there Mrs. Hammersley at home staid till 11 Mr & Mrs. Graham calld for me in their way home . Monday April 28
went to bed ½ past 11 -- Tuesday
May . ye . Ducheſs of Bolton Mr. Vesey Miſs
came home at ½ past 11 . 4 th . May Saturday
sat up writing & c till 1 in ye . Morng . Monday
May 1783 . Mr. Harpur & Lady F Harpur in ye . Morng . for some time . Mr. Vesey came
set Mrs. Glover home . at home at ½ past 11 Monday
May 1783 Mr. Spendlove in the Morng . My Uncle & Bell they all staid
went to bed at 12 14 th . Wednesday
Years notice & c . Mr. Vesey Witneſs 'd
came home at 2 in ye . Morng 17 th . . May Saturday
went to bed at 11 oClock Sunday
May fair Chapel . after Church brought
play 'd at whist -- sup 'd upstairs Thursday
conversed till 20 Min . past 11 24 th . Saturday
felt herself rather better than yesterday
Sunday -- Mr. Caton had another good Night -- came
went down with me . 26 th . Monday
went to bed ¼ after 11 Tuesday
s desire sleep in ye . House during his absence Thursday
time . they Breakfast dine & Sup with Mr. C—— , their Governeſs , in ye . Nursery except Sunday
½ past ten -- Rain all day Friday
time since her illneſs . after dinner she took
'd with us as it was Sunday
went to our Rooms at 10 Monday
retired to our Rooms before 11 -- Tuesday
had spoke to Mr . & c Thursday
June 1783 Mrs. Fenton did not Breakfast
slept at Brick Hill 9 miles more . Sunday
was quite rejoiced at my Return & ye Servts . recd . me as if I had been absent a Year
went to bed & c & c Monday June 9
paſs 'd too pleasant & agreeable a day
took leave of them for ye . Summer
Summer . Miſs Black Mr. Glover -- Mr. C Lockwood Mr. Vesey came
conversed with ye . Dſs . Dr. of Portland & Mrs. Vesey till near 12 From March 13
